From March to as recent as June 1, 2020 (because of the pandemic and stay home order for DC) I must've ordered over $500 in food from this location. Francisco (one of the delivery guys) along with the other delivery driver (Indian guy) has always delivered to my door contactless.  Even prior to the pandemic I patronized this location for about two years.  I have on my online account delivery instructions, sit the food on the floor by the door, knock and step back 6 feet.  I will open the door and retrieve the food.  This has been going on since late March, it had become so regular delivery guys noticed the pattern and would say see you in two days as they departed.  Today I opted to order though the stay at home order was lifted Friday, because I have yet to go grocery shopping.  I ordered and waited for the delivery.  Dominoes OWN message says there's 3 ways of contactless delivery. 1) pick up in the store, 2) drop off at your door with exposure and 3) curbside delivery.  Soon I get a call from the delivery driver telling me to come outside and get my pizzas, they only offer curbside delivery.  I told him he's full of it, Francisco and the other gentleman have been delivering to my door for two months now.  Gave him the intercom call number for me to buzz him in and immediately hung up.  In the interim I called the store asked to speak to the manager and was given to Mardo.  While on hold, you clearly hear the 3 contactless options.  I explained to Mardo what happened, requested my refund and he accommodated me.  That's it for me at this location, I had previously given them a good review prior to this incident.
